<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1317741" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Enyimba.jpg?resize=600%2C416&#038;ssl=1" alt="Enyimba, Abia Warriors, NPFL" width="600" height="416" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Enyimba.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Enyimba.jpg?resize=300%2C208&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Enyimba.jpg?resize=58%2C40&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Enyimba.jpg?resize=260%2C180&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Enyimba.jpg?resize=188%2C130&amp;ssl=1 188w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Enyimba.jpg?resize=560%2C388&amp;ssl=1 560w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Enyimba FC of Aba Coach, Fatai Osho, says that his team is preparing hard and poised to take advantage of Sunday’s home match against Horoya Athletic Club of Guinea in Aba. Enyimba FC of Aba, Nigeria is matched against Horoya AC, of Conakry, Guinea in the quarter-finals of the Total African Confederation Cup and its first leg will be played in Aba on March 1. Osho said his team is working on some match strategies which he would not disclose because the team would like to win the home match to make their return leg match in Conakry on March 8 easy. He said “We are doing our utmost best to ensure we play very well on Sunday because the Horoya team, we have to give it to them, they are a formidable team.” Horoya AC is doing very well at the continental level and their local league. “We will do our best to ensure we take our chances and get the desired result.
We need to get a fantastic result here in Aba to make the return leg a bit easier for us and to see that we make it to the semi-finals”, Osho said. Osho said although his team in recent past had been hamstrung by injuries, the team is picking up now and is lucky to have had “talented and well-endowed players”. He said that if a player is injured, such player could still have a great replacement to produce results from a match. He added that Enyimba would give its best to get the points to move to semi- finals after the Horoya encounters. VANGUARD After losing his first two league games as the head coach of Enyimba, Fatai Osho has masterminded an impressive change in fortune for the People’s Elephant and his side have now embarked on a good run of four games winning streak. Osho, known as the ‘Sugar Ball’ exponent has not… February 19, 2020 In "Sports" Nigeria’s flagbearers, Enyimba FC of Aba, are determined to come out unscathed away in Bamako in their Group C Day Five clash against Malian side Djoliba on tomorrow. August 17, 2018 In "News" Paul Aigbogun, the Technical Adviser of Enyimba International Football Club of Aba, on Friday said he was wary about his side’s chances in Sunday’s clash with Katsina United. January 19, 2018 In "News"